summary: Time's Up Turns a Page: Brie Larson, Tessa Thompson and USC's Stacy Smith on a "Very Simple Formula to Create Change"
title: Time's Up Turns a Page: Brie Larson, Tessa Thompson and USC's Stacy Smith on a "Very Simple Formula to Create Change"
excerpt: Inclusion strategies have sprung up aplenty, but how to really move the needle? The organization's trio take the next step by revealing how to activate Hollywood's female networks: "I'm not interested in changing hearts and minds anymore."
description: Smith, Larson and Thompson also have been on the front lines of pushing for greater inclusion in media. It was an idea sparked at a Sundance gathering hosted by Thompson in January that led to, in June, Smith’s first study analyzing the gender, race and ethnicity of film critics; Larson used her Crystal + Lucy Awards acceptance speech to draw awareness to the issue. A database for studios and publicists, Critical, was launched with Time’s Up: “We have 400 critics on there already,” says the future Captain Marvel.

summary: Nuevo póster de Captain Marvel, previo al nuevo trailer a lanzarse el día de hoy
title: Nuevo póster de Captain Marvel, previo al nuevo trailer a lanzarse el día de hoy
body:
Nuevo póster de Captain Marvel, previo al nuevo trailer a lanzarse el día de hoy

Carol Danvers (Brie Larson) es la misteriosa persona que fue buscada por Nick Fury (Samuel L. Jackson) en la última escena de Avengers: Infinity War, y ella aparecerá en el todavía sin título Avengers 4, presumiblemente para ayudar a acabar con Thanos. Pero antes de eso, ella tiene su propia historia que contar.

Cuando la película llegue a los cines el 8 de marzo de 2019, será la vigésima primera…
